I have now noticed from reading other posts that Im not alone.  Sorry if this seems like it's been posted over and over.  I have not played the game in over a year now and have recently just logged on because I miss some of the aspects of the game (running around Qeynos and stuff).  I had quit shortly after SOL because something about the game lost its appeal.  It became too chaotic and confusing and it was like logging on to a totally different game.  My mistake which really wasnt my fault was not finding a guild that became a powerguild which ultimately kept me from good items and spots in fun to go to raids.  I ultimately became a helper and took joy in helping lower levels (most of them are higher than me and have no time to stop to say hi) or just starting a new character to play. It's sad to see now all the zones I loved so much growing up in spending countless hours in are all now completely dead.  I'm a level 56 shaman and I totally feel like a newbie and getting up to 60 seems hard enough, now I need to get up to 65 and find massive sums of money for spells and items (500,000pp items? 1000pp seems like a lot to me) just so I can enjoy the game better with others?  Id rather dedicate more time to my personal life for huge gains.  I spend most of my time at the Ice Giant area.  Thank goodness for LDON though so I don't completely feel alone in that zone.

My idea for the classic server is newly dropped items, same zones with different spawns and rare spawns.  More combinable items, better trade items combined with rare drops and tougher quests, one time quests, and rare specialized abilities an average leveler could obtain to become highly desireable in guilds. Better announcements on GM events like posters on city walls. Why leave out the nonpowergamer in on the fun?  It shouldnt be all "smash and grab look at me I have all the best items in the game".  What special abilty could I gain that those people would look at a player like me and awe?  Rather than dumping more and more expansions, why not make the game better on one server with one expansion and give everyone there some fun?  My best days were level 1-25.  After that it became a rat race with only a top goal of "look at me".

Jenikat 56 Shaman Xegony

