<!-- Skin Path: /Themes/default/Skins/PostType-TextPost.ascx -->
<P>I've been playing EQ since June 2000.&nbsp; I, too would prefer a classic game where everyone is on equal terms facing the same challenges.&nbsp;&nbsp; I'm tired of obtaining keys to advance.&nbsp; I did my Vex Thal key only to head there 6 times.&nbsp; I am flagged for Time and raided in that zone longer, but not enough to merit the year long goals of becoming flagged.&nbsp;&nbsp;Right now I don't have time to put together my Anguish Key and frankly, I'm burned out on the whole flagging / keying part of EQ.&nbsp; I'm flagged / keyed for zones no one groups in.&nbsp; No one groups on the planes anymore, no one really wants to.&nbsp; And why is that?&nbsp; Loot?&nbsp; Exp?&nbsp; Boredom?&nbsp; Heck, I was in Plane of Torment for 2 weeks, gathering baking supplies.&nbsp; I was the only one there, well, except for the odd player running deeper into the zone.</P>
<P>Raid zones take hours.&nbsp; Gaining flags, keys, or even runes more time.&nbsp; The game isn't about a casual player anymore.&nbsp; If you want to keep up or remain in a raiding type guild, you have to commit to long hours.&nbsp; And I am a casual player.&nbsp; As the age base of the game is growing older, their lives change, and I bet most don't have the time for EQ as they used to.&nbsp; Of course there's always the die hard fan but I've seen more and more become casual players before finally leaving the game.</P>
<P>The game was about&nbsp;casual groupings&nbsp;of players learning a zone and learning their character to where it is now.&nbsp; Waiting on groups.&nbsp; Waiting for the right players for those groups.&nbsp; Taking up to half an hour to get to the group spot.&nbsp; Not being able to group.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Lower to mid level characters have difficulty finding players to group.&nbsp; High levels are in the same situation but theirs is by choice.&nbsp; Either they are tired of the same exp spots, they are too picky of classes in the group, they're still banned from a mission and they'd rather do that mission than anything else, or they're more interested in loot and would rather group where the loot is prime.&nbsp; Or in my case it's being burned out by long nightly raids and not wanting to spend time grouping.&nbsp; Lately I've just been logging in to raid.&nbsp; If I log in.</P>
<P>General impression here, but I feel that the upper levels aren't grouping for fun.&nbsp; It's about what they want out of the game, more self interest and goals.&nbsp; It's about gear, AA's, levels, achievements, keys, flags, and what not and it's doing all those in the most efficient manner possible.</P>
<P>I had more fun starting a newbie in the tutorial this week than I've had for a month playing my level 70 cleric.&nbsp; I have plenty of content.&nbsp; I don't want any more expansions.&nbsp; I would like to see more quality in the exsisting content.</P>

